{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chart-page-js","path":"/onion-diagram","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>is a type of non-numeric diagram that consists of concentric circles representing categories. Each outer ring represents a category that includes all of its inner circles. </p>\n<!--more-->\n<p>Onion diagrams are used to describe the relationship of several <strong><em>categories</em></strong> where one broad category is the \"outer layer\" that includes narrower categories represented by \"inner layers.\"</p>\n<p>The onion diagram does not represent quantities of its categories, but only their loose relationship to each other by using the metaphorical layers.</p>\n<p>In psychology, an example of a well-known and widely-cited onion diagram is the \"The “Onion”: Manifestations of Culture at Different Levels of Depth\" <sup id=\"fnref-1\"><a href=\"#fn-1\" class=\"footnote-ref\">1</a></sup> which describes the inner drives and outer manifestations of a culture.</p>\n<p>Onion diagrams are used to illustrate relationships between several categories, but with more than a few circles, the chart's readability declines.</p>\n<p>The onion diagram can be thought of as a Euler diagram where each set has only one subset.</p>\n<h2 id=\"alternatives\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#alternatives\" aria-label=\"alternatives permalink\" class=\"anchorLink before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Alternatives</h2>\n<p>Other metaphor-based diagrams can be used to show relationships between categories.</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"/funnel-chart\"><em>Funnel chart</em></a> starts with the top category, that represents 100%. The lower segments of the funnel represent some percentage of the top segment with a decreasing pattern.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/pyramid-diagram\"><em>Pyramid diagram</em></a> starts at the bottom with the bottom segment representing 100% and the upper segments representing some percentage of the bottom.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"further-reading\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#further-reading\" aria-label=\"further reading permalink\" class=\"anchorLink before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Further reading</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Onion_diagram\">Onion diagram</a> article on Wikipedia.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"references\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#references\" aria-label=\"references permalink\" class=\"anchorLink before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>References</h2>\n<div class=\"footnotes\">\n<hr>\n<ol>\n<li id=\"fn-1\">\n<p>Hofstede, Geert <a href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=o4OqTgV3V00C&#x26;pg=PA8\"><em>Culture and Organisations: Software of The Mind: Intercultural Cooperation and Its Importance for Survival.</em></a> McGraw-Hill (1997). p.8.</p>\n<a href=\"#fnref-1\" class=\"footnote-backref\">↩</a>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</div>","excerpt":"is a type of non-numeric diagram that consists of concentric circles representing categories. Each outer ring represents a category that…","overview":"<p>is a type of non-numeric diagram that consists of concentric circles representing categories. Each outer ring represents a category that…</p>","fields":{"variationOf":null},"frontmatter":{"title":"onion diagram","synonyms":["concentric circles diagram"],"functions":["concept visualization"],"visualizationTechniques":null,"informationTypes":null,"axisDirections":null,"examples":[{"title":"The Onion: Manifestations of Culture at Different Levels of Depth","link":"https://books.google.com/books?id=o4OqTgV3V00C&pg=PA8","note":null,"image":"hofstede-culture-onion.png"},{"title":"Concentric Circles Model of The Cultural Industries","link":"https://www.researchgate.net/figure/The-concentric-circles-model-of-the-cultural-industries_fig1_248952696","note":null,"image":"concentric-circles-model-of-the-cultural-industries.png"}],"tools":[{"name":"PowerPoint","link":"https://adioma.com"},{"name":"Apple Keynote","link":"https://www.tableau.com"}]},"fileInfo":{"__typename":"File","modifiedTime":"07/24/2023"}},"coverImage":{"publicURL":"/static/70a81fea62e069ed8b715ae0028543cf/cover.png"},"anatomyImage":{"publicURL":"/static/02dc71ae15ffd995ed6ad88c588bd0f3/anatomy.png"},"site":{"siteMetadata":{"siteUrl":"https://graphopedia.xyz"}},"exampleImages":{"edges":[{"node":{"base":"concentric-circles-model-of-the-cultural-industries.png","relativeDirectory":"charts/onion-diagram/examples","childImageSharp":{"original":{"width":697,"height":453,"src":"/static/concentric-circles-model-of-the-cultural-industries-f11b66bc5f2d0fbc45d0ca6116b714f5.png"},"fixed":{"base64"